# Efficient-Carbon-Capture: The Community Carbon Pathway

An open-source, dual-purpose public infrastructure blueprint that transforms standard municipal water spillways into interactive, carbon-capturing wading features and community hubs. 

By leveraging natural gravity-fed water, a decentralized network of solar-powered picnic pavilions, and human-powered mechanical abrasion, this system permanently removes carbon dioxide ($\text{CO}_2$) from the atmosphere and turns it into solid stone.

---

